  <div id="CSS">
      <h2>Cascading Style Sheets</h2>
      <p>CSS also known as Cascading Style Sheets was a bit of a bumpy road to start with, going into it I found the beginning a bit awkward the attempts over adn over again until it worked styling plays a 
        big part in any web page development as it is used to attract the users attention while also making it easy to navigate and use.</p>
      <p>Below is a list of what i have experienced so far.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>CSS Syntax, CSS Selectors (type/class, id/attributes, pseudo classes), CSS Dom Selectors</li>
        <li>Inline and embedded CSS, External CSS and Precedence, CSS Rules</li>
        <li>Pixels, em & rem, percentage, vh & vw</li>
        <li>Font Family, Font Color, Font Parameters, Font Position, Font Style</li>
        <li>Background Positioning, Background Appearance, Background Source</li>
        <li>Layout Interactions, Overflow and Float, Clear and Centering</li>
      </ul>
